summary:
CR Enb preset by Bigeyescarl aka abc75179778300.

Highlighted features of CR Enb series:
1. All customizable and controllable shaders via GUI panel for Enb user and tweakers to do advanced modding and tweaking.
2. Separated tweaked, fully optimized inis, and uniquely adjusted weathers.
3. Customized esps
descriptionHtml:
[size=4]Please read the following info about CR Enb carefully, especially the Requirements and installment section.[/size]
[size=4]To check that whether your rig can handle this preset or not, please refer to my other sticking post. Feel free to submit your images, and feel free to leave comments.[/size]
[size=3]-----------------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[size=3]////////////////////////////////////////////////////////[/size]
[size=4]---------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[color=#ff0000][size=5]*-2017/07/23-*[/size][/color]
[size=4][b]CR Enb [color=#6aa84f]308 Ken[/color]+ [color=#3c78d8]Cinematic Blue[/color]+ [color=#3d85c6]Cinematic Blueinkish[/color]+ [color=#38761d]Cinematic Greenish[/color] uploaded and ready to download. Enjoy the final work of my preset! [/b][/size]
[size=4]Info about the above mentioned 4 presets:

[color=#ff0000]1. Ken[/color] -> Epic preset with a touch of cinematic adopted of darkened green color and tints but still, the realistic atmosphere was kept with contrast boost, my second favorite presets with hundreds of hours of adjustment.

[color=#ff0000]2. Cinematic Blue[/color] -> Best of my cinematic series alive again in 308 series with blue tinting but not that overdone.

[color=#ff0000]3. Cinematic Blueinkish[/color] -> Another adoption with sepia effect on, more desaturated than Cinematic Blue.

[color=#ff0000]4. Cinematic Greenish[/color] -> The other preset adopted to meet a bit of green colored, looks great too.

[/size][size=5]**See the 308R section for requirement and installation, and plz refer to the image section for [color=#3d85c6]load order(same as 308R)[/color]**.

[color=#cc0000]PS:[/color] 'Tis not a short neither a long journey during these three years of modding, CK using and codes writing were drew from these days I spent on Enb making and tweaking, and the time for leaving this behind and pursue other goals of mine has came. See you guys in TES6, and farewell for now.
[/size][size=3]-----------------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[size=3]////////////////////////////////////////////////////////[/size]
[size=4]---------------------------------------------------------------[/size]

[size=4]How to[/size][b][color=#ff0000][size=5] turn off Letter Box effect[/size][/color][/b][size=4]? Follow the following simply steps, plz:[/size]

[size=4]First, go to the folder called "enbseries", and find the ini file named enbeffect.fx.[/size]
[size=4]Open the enbeffect.fx ini and found this line, LB: Letter box size, in %=8.0, simply alter it to, LB: Letter box size, in %=0.0, and there you go without LetterBox effect.
I just recalled that I forgot to set the default preset without letterbox effect, oh forgetful me.

[/size][b][size=5][color=#ff0000]*[/color][color=#ffff00]-2017/07/17-[/color][color=#ff0000]*[/color][/size][/b]
[size=6][color=#f4f4f4]CR Enb 308 Series , [/color][color=#ff0000]CR Enb Ken Edition[/color][color=#f4f4f4] coming [/color][color=#1e84cc]this weekend![/color][/size]

[b][size=5]Info about the upcoming CR Enb 308R (308R = realistic version) preset:[/size][/b]

[font=Georgia][size=4][color=#00ff00]1. [/color]Made with the high contrast greenish toned palette making it more darkening than 308R.
[color=#00ff00]2. [/color]Epic overcast and raining day.
[color=#00ff00]3. [/color]All weathers independently adjusted.
[color=#00ff00]4. [/color]Optional files include in all in one package, for easy tuning.
[/size][/font]
[b][size=5][color=#ff0000]*[/color][color=#ffff00]-2017/07/01-[/color][color=#ff0000]*[/color][/size][/b][b][size=6]
[color=#ff0000]CR Enb 308 Series , CR Enb 308R (Realistic ver) released![/color]
[font=Lucida Sans Unicode]
[/font][/size][/b][font=Lucida Sans Unicode][size=4]Info about the upcoming CR Enb 308R (308R = realistic version) preset:[/size]

[size=4][color=#e06666]1. [/color]Made without any palette ensuring that the tone-mapping formula works like charm and tint-less.
[color=#e06666]2.[/color] Users approved color-filters and black white level-adjusted for smooth and long time gaming experience, and the beauty of SSS of old 292 Realistic Version also retained. 
[color=#e06666]3.[/color] Diverse lens flare effect as options for users to select.
[color=#e06666]4.[/color] New biological functioned DoF based on Matso's Dof, for long time gaming.
[color=#e06666]5.[/color] Final adjusted all weathers independently (Vanilla+All DLC+CoT weathers) 
[color=#e06666]6.[/color] Optional files include in all in one package, for easy tuning.
[/size][size=4][color=#e06666]7.[/color] [b][u]Other presets[/u] would[/b] be introduced soon. 

[b][color=#ff0000]*Screenshots of 308R[/color][/b] were at the front of my image section, though some of them I placed at the bottom of image section, go and see for yourself before downloading this preset.* And plz note that all the screenshots were taken directly in game, no further photoshoping or parameters tweaking.
[color=#ff0000]Recommendation and notes to the users:[/color]

[color=#ff0000]*[/color]For the best looking of your characters, highly recommended using [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/58443/?]Skysights male textures[/url], as for female, [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/32986/?]mature skin[/url] is without a doubt the best to go along with version 308R. 
Please also note that other skin textures would not look that good as you perceive they were in old 292 version. And why? For 292 realistic ver,  there was a yellowish mixed with orange tinted palette in use when making it, it turned out that the warming tone would be a make up for the textures and enhance the skin of character, though the disadvantages were more than the gain of beautication of character, and it turned out that I found a balance without palette in 308R. That's the reason why 292 still got labelled as the main file, for there were uses prefer the characters tone of 292 other than 308. I personally prefer 308R with skysight male skin and mature skin installed, looks great than 292 and that's what I could say unless I'm tastelss in the skin texture. 
[color=#ff0000]**[/color]For best gaming experience plz also go for [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/39450/?]Real clouds[/url], for the best immersive gaming experience while applying this preset.
[color=#ff0000][size=6][b][font=Courier New]*Requirements*[/font]:[/b][/size][/color]

[b][font=Times New Roman][size=6]1. [color=#93c47d]PureWater[/color] or [color=#93c47d]RW2[/color]
2. [color=#f1c232]ELFX 3.0 [/color]
3.[color=#3c78d8] CoT V5.0
[/color]4. [color=#38761d]Vivid Clouds and Fogs - Vanilla and Climates of Tamriel [/color][color=#e06666](textures included in 308R package, and other alternative cloud textures made by me also included, essential for 308 and above series!)[/color]

[b][size=6][color=#ff0000]*Important note of 308 Series*:
[/color]
[/size][size=4]**All of my presets [color=#ff0000]do not[/color] compatible with[color=#ff0000] Remove Exterior Fog[/color] and [color=#ff0000]Revamped Exterior Fog[/color].**
**[color=#ff0000]Do not[/color] use other COT Weather Patches as the CR ENB already covered these.**
**Use ELFX MOD without Enhancer.esp ( use Enhancer esp only if you still feel the interior and dungeons look too bright.)**

[/size][/b][/size][/font][/b][/size][/font]

[b][color=#ff0000][size=5]*-2016/11/07-*
[/size][/color][/b][b][size=6][i]CR Enb 292 Realistic Ver released[/i].[/size][/b]
[size=4]Please scroll down and  read the requirement and [/size][size=4]installation sections before downloading this preset.
Esp load order is the same as 272 beta ver. See the image section for more images.
Please be aware that due to the mods used of each user, setting, and the differences of every monitor, the final result would be slightly different in game.
Set the "contrast", "color grading or grey grading" and "R","G","B" parameters to 50 in your monitor setting to experience  the similar result I would like my preset users to observe.

[color=#ffff00][u][b]Features[/b][/u] [/color]compared to 272 Realistic beta ver:
1. Enhance SSS.
2. Enhance ambient lighting/lens flares/weathers/water.
3.  Performance friendly.

Have fun and happy gaming ;)[/size]
[size=4]------------------------------------------------------------
////////////////////////////////////////////////
------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[b][size=5][i]Tutorial Installation Guide[/i] by  [i][color=#3c78d8]Heisenn burgg [/color][/i][/size][/b]
[b][color=#ff0000][size=5]-2015/07/31-[/size][/color][/b][size=6]
[youtube]iBjbFd5ctp4[/youtube][/size][size=5][b]
[/b][/size][size=3]---------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[size=3]/////////////////////////////////////////////[/size]
[size=3]---------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[b][color=#ff0000][size=5]-2015/06/28-
[/size][/color][/b][size=5]CR Realistic 272 Beta available now.[/size][size=4]
[/size][size=3]---------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[size=3]/////////////////////////////////////////////[/size]
[size=3]---------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[b][size=6][color=#ff0000]*Important note*:
[/color]
[/size][size=4][color=#ff0000]**[/color]All of my presets [color=#ff0000]do not compatible[/color] with [color=#e06666]Remove Exterior Fog[/color] and [color=#e06666]Revamped Exterior Fog[/color].[color=#ff0000]**
[/color][color=#ff0000]**[/color]Use Main COT 3.1 and it's Expansions for DG, DB. Do not use other COT Weather Patches as the CR ENB already covered these.[color=#ff0000]**[/color]
[color=#ff0000]**[/color]Use ELFX MOD minus Enhancer.esp ( use Enhancer esp only if you still feel the interior and dungeons look kinda bright.)[color=#ff0000]**[/color][/size]
[/b]
[color=#ff0000][size=6][b][font=Courier New]*Requirements*[/font]:[/b][/size][/color]

[b][font=Times New Roman][size=6]1. [color=#93c47d]PureWater[/color] 
2. [color=#f1c232]ELFX 2.0 [/color]or [b][font=Times New Roman][color=#f1c232][size=6]ELE (ELE V094 or above version that comes with a single legendary esp will do)[/size][/color][/font][/b]
3.[color=#3c78d8] CoT and all CoT patches from jjc71.
[/color]4. [color=#38761d]Vivid Clouds and Fogs - Vanilla and Climates of Tamriel [/color][color=#e06666](not essential but highly recommended as I used this texture pack to make this preset)[/color]
[/size][/font][/b]
[b][color=#ff0000][size=6]*Features*[/size][/color][size=6][color=#ff0000]:[/color]
[/size][/b][size=5]1. Customized CoT Weather esp with every one of the weathers modified. 
2. Eye adaption tint like the Witcher 3 but not that over toned.
3. A nicely tweaked preset.[/size]

[size=4]---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[size=4]----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------[/size]
[color=#3c78d8][size=6][b]Installation[/b]:[/size][/color]

[b][size=4]Step I. Download the consistent version ENB binary on Enb official website and copy the "d3d9.dll" to your skyrim folder.[/size]

[size=4]Step II. Copy all of the files in the Main folder to where Skyrim.exe is (usually locate at Steam/SteamApps/common/Skyrim).[/size]

[size=4]Step III. Editing the following lines in SkyrimPrefs.ini; if one of the line doesn't exist, just copy the following like and paste it to under the [Display section][/size]

[size=4][Display][/size]
[size=4]bFloatPointRenderTarget=1[/size]
[size=4]bTreesReceiveShadows=1[/size]
[size=4]bDrawLandShadows=1[/size]
[size=4]bShadowsOnGrass=1
[/size]
[size=4]Step IV. Use NMM to check the CR Enb esp. along with CR ENB Snow FX and Pure Water esp (modified).[/size]

[size=4]Step V. Make sure you save indoors before applying or installing my enb preset.[/size][/b]

[color=#6aa84f][size=6]Uninstallation:[/size]
[/color]
[size=4]Delete the enb related files in the main folders or use enbremover for quick removing and arranging preset. [/size]
